	<h2>General Introduction</h2>
	<p>
		I’ve always been a girl who loves science and logic, right from a young age.
		I guess I’m a bit different from most girls—I was never really into books or Barbie dolls; instead, I fell in love with scale models and cars. During middle and high school, I realized my true passions lay in math and physics, especially geometry and mechanics. Back then, my dream was to go into scientific research.
		Before even finishing high school, I was selected for the Science and Technology Scholarship, which brought me to NTU, somewhat wide-eyed and green. 
		Now, as a Computer Science major, I genuinely enjoy writing interesting code and love experimenting with new things. My ultimate dream is to create or conduct research in a field I love—to discover something entirely new or build novel products. 
		I’m still on this journey of continuous exploration, hoping to eventually find what truly resonates with my soul.
	</p>

